column1: <U>Unfortunately this is one of those, but I will say that the action scenes were well made and people who go to shows simply for action won't be to disappointed.<C><U>Hey have you seen Gemini Man yet?<A>No not yet, how was it?<U>Well I have mixed feelings about it. Will Smith is one of my favorite actors and has made some of my favorite films, like I Am Legend, 7 Pounds, and The Pursuit of Happiness. But i'm not getting that same feeling from his latest film.<A>Oh I understand that, he's one of my favorite actors too and i've cried from just about all those movies because they were so touching and the suspense was incredible.<U>Right that's what I mean he really captured the audience with those films but this newest film didn't do that for me.<A>Well that's somewhat understandable being that it's an action film.<U>I know that, but even still the story just didn't hold my attention like the others did.<A>So you're saying the story was a bit bland?<U>Yes. but it was also somewhat incoherent and they tried to make up for the holes in the story with fast paced action scenes.<A>That's unfortunate because i was looking forward to a suspenseful thriller like his previous films.<U>Yeah me too, I really enjoy films that leave you wondering about the ending, or ones that make you think and pay attention to clues throughout.<A>Absolutely when a movie can throw you off and keep you guessing that it a great feeling. I never like being able to figure out an ending before the movie is over.
